The article discusses World Freedom Day, which commemorates the fall of the Berlin Wall in 1989 and honors those who peacefully fought for freedom. It acknowledges the progress made in advancing human rights and democracy since then, but also highlights the fragility of democracy and the threats it faces from authoritarianism. The United States is committed to supporting democratic renewal and resilience globally, and will host a virtual Summit for Democracy to address these issues. The article concludes with a proclamation by President Joseph R. Biden Jr., calling upon the American people to remember the hope symbolized by the fall of the Berlin Wall and reaffirm their dedication to freedom and democracy.